 societies." -Michèle Lagny, Université de Sorbonne Nouvelle Paris III  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aHomosexuality in motion pictures. 0aHuman body in motion pictures. 0aMotion pictures -- Spain -- History. 0aMotion pictures, SpanishxHistory. 0aWomen in motion pictures. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013z978311070067108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060651508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z97831106627880 cprintz978908964303240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048514038?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048514038zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048514038/original  a978-3-11-060651-5 AUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066278-8 Amsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2002d2015  a978-3-11-070067-1 AUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA